    3. Fault Confirmation

    Effective on: 001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-710-052 -A0 - (20151101)

    A. Test
    (1) Do only the test of the integral lighting of the overhead panel SEE AMM 33-13-00-710-001 .


    Effective on:  001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894
    Instrument and Panel Integral Lighting

    If, during this operational test, on the INT LT section of the overhead control and indicating panel 25VU:

    •

    When you turn the OVHD INTEG LT potentiometer (7LF) from OFF to BRT SEE ASM 33-13-02 :

    (a) One light of one integral-lighted identification plate does not operate, go to Para 4.A.
    (b) The integral lighting of one instrument or panel does not operate, go to Para 4.B.
    (c) The integral lighting of more than one instruments and/or panels connected to the same fuse output do not operate, go to Para 4.C.
    (d) The integral lighting of all the panels and/or the instruments do not operate, go to Para. 4.D.

    Effective on: 875, 877-893, 895-910, 928-950, 986-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-710-052 -B0 - (20170501)

    A. Test
    (1) Do only the test of the integral lighting of the overhead panel SEE AMM 33-13-00-710-001 .

    •

    If, during this operational test, on the INT LT section of the overhead control and indicating panel 25VU:

    When you turn the OVHD INTEG LT potentiometer (7LF) from OFF to BRT SEE ASM 33-13-02 :

    (a) The integral lighting of one identification plate does not operate, go to Para 4.A.
    (b) The integral lighting of one instrument or panel does not operate, go to Para 4.B.
    (c) The integral lighting of more than one instrument or panel connected to the same fuse output does not operate, go to Para 4.C.
    (d) The integral lighting of all the panels and/or the instruments do not operate, go to Para. 4.D.
    (e) The integral lighting of more than one panels connected to the same pulse width modulation output do not operate, go to Para 4.E.

    4. Fault Isolation

    Effective on: 001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-051 -A0 - (20151101)

    A. One light of one integral-lighted identification-plate does not operate
    (1) Remove the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-42-000-001 .
    (2) Replace the defective lamp of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate.
    NOTE:   
    Refer to the applicable CMM related to the P/N of the integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AIPC 33-13-08 for removal/installation instructions.
    (3) Install the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-42-400-001 .

    Effective on: 875, 877-893, 895-910, 928-950, 986-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-051 -B0 - (20170501)

    A. The integral lighting of one plate does not operate.
    (1) Remove the related integrally-lighted identification-plate, SEE AMM 33-13-42-000-001 .
    (2) Do a check for continuity between the pin A/1 of the electrical connector of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate and the first terminal block SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    (a) If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring  between pin A/1 of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate and the first terminal block.

    (b) If there is continuity:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/N of the instrument or the panel, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-42-400-001 .

    2 If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    •

    Install the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-42-400-001 .


    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-054 -A0 - (20160501)

    B. The integral lighting of one instrument or panel does not operate
    NOTE:   
    All the instruments or panels that follow are possible causes. If one or several instrument(s) and/or panel(s) is(are) not installed for your aircraft, the troubleshooting of instrument(s) and/or panel(s) that is(are) not installed is(are) not applicable.
    (1) FOR 2RN3 (ACP-3RD OCCPNT)
    (a) Remove the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3) SEE AMM 23-51-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/A of the electrical connector of the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring  between pin A/A of the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/B of the electrical connector of the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace ACP-3RD OCCPNT (2RN3)   SEE AMM 23-51-12-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3) pin A/B to the terminal ground.

    •

    Install the Third Occupant ACP (2RN3) SEE AMM 23-51-12-400-001 .

    (2) FOR 2RN5
    (a) Remove the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5) SEE AMM 23-51-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/A of the electrical connector of the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring  between pin A/A of the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/B of the electrical connector of the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (2RN5)   SEE AMM 23-51-12-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5) pin A/A to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the Fourth Occupant ACP (2RN5) SEE AMM 23-51-12-400-001 .

    (3) FOR 3PV1 (VOLTMETER-BAT 1)
    (a) Remove the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1) SEE AMM 24-37-21-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin E of the electrical connector of the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin E of the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin K of the electrical connector of the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace VOLTMETER-BAT 1 (3PV1)   SEE AMM 24-37-21-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1) pin E to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the battery 1 voltmeter (3PV1) SEE AMM 24-37-21-400-001 .

    (4) FOR 3PV2 (VOLTMETER-BAT 2)
    (a) Remove the (3PV2) SEE AMM 24-37-21-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin E of the electrical connector of the battery 2 voltmeter (3PV2), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin E of the battery 2 voltmeter (3PV2) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin K of the electrical connector of the battery 2 voltmeter (3PV2), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace VOLTMETER-BAT 2 (3PV2)   SEE AMM 24-37-21-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the battery 2 voltmeter (3PV2) pin E to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the battery 2 voltmeter (3PV2) SEE AMM 24-37-21-400-001 .

    (5) FOR 111MX (CONTROL PANEL-REMOTE,ELT)
    (a) Remove the ELT remote control-panel (111MX) SEE AMM 25-65-18-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/K of the electrical connector of the ELT remote control-panel (111MX), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin A/K of the ELT remote control-panel (111MX) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/L of the electrical connector of the ELT remote control-panel (111MX), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace CONTROL PANEL-REMOTE,ELT (111MX)   SEE AMM 25-65-18-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the ELT remote control-panel (111MX) pin A/L to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the ELT remote control-panel (111MX) SEE AMM 25-65-18-400-001 .

    (6) FOR 940WR
    (a) Remove the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR) SEE AMM 35-23-22-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/E of the electrical connector of the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin A/E of the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/D of the electrical connector of the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (940WR)   SEE AMM 35-23-22-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR) pin A/D to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the passenger-oxygen cockpit indication-panel (940WR) SEE AMM 35-23-22-400-001 .

    (7) FOR 2RZ
    (a) Remove the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ) SEE AMM 23-14-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/20 of the electrical connector of the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between the pin A/20 of the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/24 of the electrical connector of the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (2RZ)   SEE AMM 23-14-12-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ) pin A/20 to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the crypto-voice control panel (2RZ) SEE AMM 23-14-12-400-001 .

    (8) FOR 10QT
    (a) Remove the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT) SEE AMM 28-42-21-000-002 .
    (b) Do a check of voltage on the pin A/H of the electrical connector of the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between the pin A/H of the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/J of the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (10QT)   SEE AMM 28-42-21-400-002 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT) pin A/H to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the cockpit fuel-quantity preselector (10QT) SEE AMM 28-42-21-400-002 .

    (9) FOR 1WD (ENG/APU FIRE PNL)
    (a) Remove the engine/APU fire panel (1WD) SEE AMM 26-12-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin E/Z of the electrical connector of the engine/APU fire panel (1WD), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin E/Z of the engine/APU fire panel (1WD) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin E/a of the engine/APU fire panel (1WD), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace ENG/APU FIRE PNL (1WD)   SEE AMM 26-12-12-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the engine/APU fire panel (1WD) pin E/Z to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the engine/APU fire panel (1WD) SEE AMM 26-12-12-400-001 .

    (10) FOR 81QT
    (a) Remove the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT) SEE AMM 28-42-23-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/H of the electrical connector of the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin A/H of the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/J of the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (81QT)   SEE AMM 28-42-23-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT) pin A/H to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the cockpit multi-tank indicator (81QT) SEE AMM 28-42-23-400-001 .

    (11) FOR 1RG3
    (a) Remove the communication-frequency selector RPM 3 (1RG3) SEE AMM 23-13-13-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/T of the electrical connector of the communication-frequency selector RPM 3 (1RG3), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin A/T of the communication-frequency selector RMP 3 (1RG3) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/U of the communication-frequency selector RPM 3 (1RG3), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (1RG3)   SEE AMM 23-13-13-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the communication-frequency selector RMP 3 (1RG3) to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the communication-frequency selector RPM 3 (1RG3) SEE AMM 23-13-13-400-001 .

    (12) FOR 2FP
    (a) Remove the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP) SEE AMM 34-12-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/1 of the electrical connector of the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring between pin A/1 of the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP) and the first terminal block.

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/U of the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP), SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (2FP)   SEE AMM 34-12-12-400-001 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP) pin A/1 to the ground terminal.

    •

    Install the control and display unit of the ADIRS (2FP) SEE AMM 23-13-13-400-001 .


    Effective on: 001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-055 -A0 - (20151101)

    C. The integral lighting of more than one instrument and/or panels connected to the same fuse output does not operate.


    Effective on:  001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894
    Integral Lighting Controller Overhead 6 LF

    (1) For fuse output K:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/K of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    2 If there is continuity:
    •

    Replace CONTROLLER-LIGHTING (6LF)   SEE AMM 33-13-51-000-001 and SEE AMM 33-13-51-400-001 .

    (2) For fuse output J:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/J of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    2 If there is continuity:
    •

    Replace CONTROLLER-LIGHTING (6LF)   SEE AMM 33-13-51-000-001 and SEE AMM 33-13-51-400-001 .

    (3) For fuse output H:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/H of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    2 If there is continuity:
    •

    Replace CONTROLLER-LIGHTING (6LF)   SEE AMM 33-13-51-000-001 and SEE AMM 33-13-51-400-001 .

    (4) For fuse output L:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/L of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    2 If there is continuity:
    •

    Replace CONTROLLER-LIGHTING (6LF)   SEE AMM 33-13-51-000-001 and SEE AMM 33-13-51-400-001 .

    (5) For fuse output N:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/N of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:

    (6) For fuse output M:
    •

    Do a check of the fuse.
    (a) If the fuse is not correct:
    •

    Replace the fuse  .

    (b) If the fuse is correct:
    •

    Do a check for continuity between pin A/M of the electrical connector of the lighting controller (6LF) and the first terminal block, SEE ASM 33-13-02 .

    1 If there is no continuity:

    2 If there is continuity:

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-056 -A0 - (20151101)

    D. The integral lighting of all the panels and/or the instruments does not operate.
